<!doctype html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="utf-8">
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1">
  <title>Dzukku Business Brochure</title>
  <style>
    @page {
      size: A4;
      margin: 0;
    }

    :root {
      --ink: #18222f;
      --muted: #657180;
      --soft: #f7f4ee;
      --paper: #ffffff;
      --line: #dde5ec;
      --brand: #bf342e;
      --brand-dark: #7d1821;
      --orange: #ff7043;
      --gold: #c48a2c;
      --green: #12966f;
      --blue: #2764a8;
      --night: #111421;
    }

    * {
      box-sizing: border-box;
    }

    html,
    body {
      margin: 0;
      background: #e8edf2;
      color: var(--ink);
      font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;
      line-height: 1.45;
    }

    body {
      -webkit-print-color-adjust: exact;
      print-color-adjust: exact;
    }

    .page {
      width: 210mm;
      min-height: 297mm;
      margin: 0 auto;
      padding: 18mm;
      background: var(--paper);
      position: relative;
      overflow: hidden;
      page-break-after: always;
    }

    .page:last-child {
      page-break-after: auto;
    }

    .cover {
      color: #fff;
      padding: 0;
      background:
        linear-gradient(135deg, rgba(125, 24, 33, 0.98), rgba(15, 18, 30, 0.96) 52%, rgba(13, 31, 55, 0.95)),
        radial-gradient(circle at 18% 12%, rgba(255, 112, 67, 0.36), transparent 28%),
        radial-gradient(circle at 88% 84%, rgba(39, 100, 168, 0.42), transparent 32%);
    }

    .cover-inner {
      height: 297mm;
      padding: 22mm 18mm;
      display: flex;
      flex-direction: column;
      justify-content: space-between;
    }

    .eyebrow {
      margin: 0 0 12px;
      color: #ffd4b5;
      font-size: 10px;
      font-weight: 800;
      letter-spacing: 2px;
      text-transform: uppercase;
    }

    h1,
    h2,
    h3,
    p {
      margin-top: 0;
    }

    h1 {
      max-width: 168mm;
      margin-bottom: 14px;
      font-size: 46px;
      line-height: 1.04;
      letter-spacing: -0.4px;
    }

    .cover-subtitle {
      max-width: 160mm;
      color: #f3e7df;
      font-size: 18px;
      line-height: 1.45;
    }

    .cover-grid {
      display: grid;
      grid-template-columns: repeat(4, 1fr);
      gap: 10px;
      margin-top: 22px;
    }

    .cover-card {
      min-height: 31mm;
      padding: 12px;
      border: 1px solid rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.22);
      border-radius: 12px;
      background: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.08);
    }

    .cover-card strong {
      display: block;
      margin-bottom: 4px;
      font-size: 15px;
    }

    .cover-card span {
      color: #ead7cd;
      font-size: 11px;
    }

    .cover-shot {
      margin-top: 22px;
      border-radius: 18px;
      border: 1px solid rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.22);
      box-shadow: 0 22px 52px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.38);
      overflow: hidden;
      background: #0c0f1a;
    }

    .cover-shot img {
      display: block;
      width: 100%;
      max-height: 110mm;
      object-fit: cover;
      object-position: top center;
    }

    .cover-footer {
      display: flex;
      justify-content: space-between;
      gap: 16px;
      align-items: end;
      color: #e6d9d0;
      font-size: 12px;
    }

    .section-kicker {
      margin-bottom: 6px;
      color: var(--brand);
      font-size: 10px;
      font-weight: 800;
      letter-spacing: 1.7px;
      text-transform: uppercase;
    }

    h2 {
      margin-bottom: 11px;
      color: var(--brand-dark);
      font-size: 29px;
      line-height: 1.08;
      letter-spacing: -0.2px;
    }

    h3 {
      margin-bottom: 7px;
      color: #243141;
      font-size: 16px;
      line-height: 1.22;
    }

    p,
    li,
    td,
    th {
      font-size: 12.2px;
    }

    p {
      margin-bottom: 9px;
    }

    .lead {
      max-width: 168mm;
      color: #374656;
      font-size: 16px;
      line-height: 1.5;
    }

    .muted {
      color: var(--muted);
    }

    .grid-2 {
      display: grid;
      grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
      gap: 12px;
    }

    .grid-3 {
      display: grid;
      grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr);
      gap: 10px;
    }

    .card {
      padding: 13px;
      border: 1px solid var(--line);
      border-radius: 12px;
      background: #fff;
      break-inside: avoid;
    }

    .card.tint {
      border-color: #f0d3c4;
      background: #fff8f2;
    }

    .metric {
      display: block;
      margin-bottom: 5px;
      color: var(--orange);
      font-size: 26px;
      font-weight: 900;
      line-height: 1;
    }

    .callout {
      margin: 12px 0;
      padding: 15px 16px;
      border-left: 5px solid var(--gold);
      border-radius: 10px;
      background: #fff8e8;
      color: #3a2d1e;
      font-size: 13px;
    }

    table {
      width: 100%;
      border-collapse: collapse;
      margin-top: 8px;
      overflow: hidden;
      border-radius: 10px;
    }

    th,
    td {
      padding: 9px 10px;
      border: 1px solid var(--line);
      text-align: left;
      vertical-align: top;
    }

    th {
      background: #eef3f6;
      color: #26313c;
      font-weight: 800;
    }

    .flow {
      display: grid;
      grid-template-columns: repeat(5, 1fr);
      gap: 8px;
      margin-top: 12px;
    }

    .flow-step {
      min-height: 33mm;
      padding: 11px 10px;
      border: 1px solid var(--line);
      border-radius: 12px;
      background: #f9fbfc;
      color: #2f3b49;
      font-size: 11px;
      line-height: 1.35;
    }

    .flow-step span {
      display: inline-grid;
      place-items: center;
      width: 24px;
      height: 24px;
      margin-bottom: 8px;
      border-radius: 50%;
      background: var(--brand);
      color: #fff;
      font-weight: 900;
      font-size: 12px;
    }

    .flow-step strong {
      display: block;
      margin-bottom: 5px;
      color: #162231;
      font-size: 13px;
      line-height: 1.18;
    }

    .screenshot {
      padding: 10px;
      border: 1px solid var(--line);
      border-radius: 14px;
      background: #fff;
      box-shadow: 0 14px 30px rgba(24, 34, 47, 0.08);
      break-inside: avoid;
    }

    .screenshot img {
      display: block;
      width: 100%;
      border: 1px solid #d4dde7;
      border-radius: 10px;
    }

    .screenshot h3 {
      margin: 10px 0 5px;
      color: var(--brand-dark);
    }

    .phone-grid {
      display: grid;
      grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr);
      gap: 8px;
      align-items: start;
    }

    .phone-shot {
      padding: 8px;
    }

    .phone-shot img {
      height: 122mm;
      max-height: 122mm;
      object-fit: contain;
      background: #111;
    }

    .phone-shot h3 {
      margin-top: 8px;
      font-size: 13.5px;
      line-height: 1.2;
    }

    .phone-shot p {
      font-size: 10.8px;
      line-height: 1.35;
    }

    .mini-label {
      display: inline-block;
      margin-bottom: 6px;
      padding: 4px 8px;
      border-radius: 999px;
      background: #f3efe8;
      color: var(--brand-dark);
      font-size: 10px;
      font-weight: 800;
      text-transform: uppercase;
      letter-spacing: 0.8px;
    }

    .footer-note {
      position: absolute;
      right: 18mm;
      bottom: 9mm;
      left: 18mm;
      display: flex;
      justify-content: space-between;
      gap: 12px;
      padding-top: 8px;
      border-top: 1px solid var(--line);
      color: #8a95a3;
      font-size: 10px;
    }

    .dark-band {
      margin: 16px -18mm 0;
      padding: 15mm 18mm;
      color: #fff;
      background:
        linear-gradient(135deg, rgba(125, 24, 33, 0.94), rgba(17, 20, 33, 0.98) 58%, rgba(13, 31, 55, 0.96));
    }

    .dark-band h2,
    .dark-band h3 {
      color: #fff;
    }

    .dark-band p,
    .dark-band li {
      color: #ded8d7;
    }

    .dark-band .flow-step {
      border-color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.28);
      background: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.94);
      color: #293746;
      box-shadow: 0 12px 26px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.18);
    }

    .dark-band .flow-step strong {
      color: #172231;
    }

    .dark-card {
      padding: 13px;
      border: 1px solid rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.18);
      border-radius: 12px;
      background: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.08);
    }

    ul,
    ol {
      margin: 7px 0 0 18px;
      padding: 0;
    }

    li {
      margin-bottom: 4px;
    }

    @media print {
      html,
      body {
        background: #fff;
      }

      .page {
        margin: 0;
        box-shadow: none;
      }
    }
  </style>
</head>
<body>
  <section class="page cover">
    <div class="cover-inner">
      <div>
        <p class="eyebrow">Business Product Brochure</p>
        <h1>Dzukku: AI Ordering And Restaurant Operations In One Platform</h1>
        <p class="cover-subtitle">
          A practical restaurant growth platform that helps businesses accept direct orders, manage staff workflows,
          coordinate kitchen execution, and understand daily performance from one connected system.
        </p>
        <div class="cover-grid">
          <div class="cover-card"><strong>Customer Chat</strong><span>Order through familiar chat and quick actions.</span></div>
          <div class="cover-card"><strong>Live Operations</strong><span>Orders, kitchen, tables, delivery, billing.</span></div>
          <div class="cover-card"><strong>Owner Visibility</strong><span>Revenue, order status, demand, trends.</span></div>
          <div class="cover-card"><strong>Scalable Model</strong><span>Single restaurant, cloud kitchen, or chain.</span></div>
        </div>
        <div class="cover-shot">
          <img src="assets/business-brochure/03-dashboard.png" alt="Dzukku dashboard preview">
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="cover-footer">
        <span>Prepared for business owners, operators, and decision-makers</span>
        <span>Project Dzukku</span>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="page">
    <p class="section-kicker">Executive Understanding</p>
    <h2>What Is Dzukku?</h2>
    <p class="lead">
      Dzukku is an AI-powered restaurant ordering and operations platform. Customers order through chat, while the
      restaurant team manages orders, kitchen preparation, table service, delivery, invoices, and analytics from a
      role-based POS workspace.
    </p>
    <div class="callout">
      In simple terms: Dzukku talks to the customer, captures the order, sends it to the right team, tracks the work,
      and gives the owner a clear view of the business.
    </div>
    <div class="grid-3">
      <div class="card tint">
        <span class="metric">1</span>
        <h3>Customers order naturally</h3>
        <p>Through Telegram, WhatsApp-style chat, QR links, and simple buttons such as Menu, Order, Cart, and Reserve.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="card tint">
        <span class="metric">2</span>
        <h3>Staff work from live queues</h3>
        <p>Admin, waiter, and kitchen teams see the right screen for their role and work from the same order flow.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="card tint">
        <span class="metric">3</span>
        <h3>Owners gain control</h3>
        <p>Daily orders, pending load, revenue, top activity, and operations become visible instead of scattered.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
    <table>
      <thead>
        <tr>
          <th>Business Question</th>
          <th>Dzukku Answer</th>
        </tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr>
          <td>Who is it for?</td>
          <td>Restaurants, cafes, cloud kitchens, QSRs, food courts, hotels, and multi-branch food businesses.</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td>What does it replace?</td>
          <td>Scattered ordering over calls, chats, spreadsheets, handwritten tickets, disconnected dashboards, and manual follow-up.</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td>Why should a business care?</td>
          <td>It can improve direct ordering, service speed, kitchen clarity, customer ownership, reporting, and branch scalability.</td>
        </tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>
    <div class="footer-note"><span>Dzukku Business Brochure</span><span>Executive Overview</span></div>
  </section>

  <section class="page">
    <p class="section-kicker">Business Challenge</p>
    <h2>The Problem Restaurants Face Today</h2>
    <p class="lead">
      Restaurants do not only need online ordering. They need an operating system that connects customer demand with
      kitchen execution and business visibility.
    </p>
    <div class="grid-2">
      <div class="card">
        <h3>Heavy aggregator dependency</h3>
        <p>Marketplaces are useful for discovery, but repeat customers often still go through commission-heavy channels.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="card">
        <h3>Scattered operations</h3>
        <p>Orders, tables, reservations, kitchen status, delivery, and billing may live in different tools or staff memory.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="card">
        <h3>Customer app fatigue</h3>
        <p>Customers do not want another complicated ordering app. They want quick recommendations and simple confirmation.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="card">
        <h3>Limited owner visibility</h3>
        <p>Owners need to know what is selling, what is delayed, what is pending, and where the business can improve.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="dark-band">
      <p class="section-kicker">Business Outcome</p>
      <h2>Dzukku connects the full restaurant journey.</h2>
      <div class="flow">
        <div class="flow-step"><span>1</span><strong>Customer asks</strong><br>Chat, QR, menu, reservation, or quick reorder.</div>
        <div class="flow-step"><span>2</span><strong>AI assists</strong><br>Recommends, confirms, and collects details.</div>
        <div class="flow-step"><span>3</span><strong>Order appears</strong><br>Admin/POS receives a structured order.</div>
        <div class="flow-step"><span>4</span><strong>Kitchen executes</strong><br>Items move pending, cooking, done.</div>
        <div class="flow-step"><span>5</span><strong>Owner learns</strong><br>Revenue, orders, delays, and demand become visible.</div>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="footer-note"><span>Dzukku Business Brochure</span><span>Business Challenge</span></div>
  </section>

  <section class="page">
    <p class="section-kicker">Product Modules</p>
    <h2>What The Product Includes</h2>
    <p class="lead">
      Dzukku is a connected set of business modules, not a single chatbot. Each module maps to a real restaurant workflow.
    </p>
    <div class="grid-3">
      <div class="card"><h3>AI Ordering Assistant</h3><p>Conversational menu help, item selection, cart, customer details, confirmation, and channel choice.</p></div>
      <div class="card"><h3>POS Command Center</h3><p>Live dashboard for orders, revenue, pending load, kitchen count, invoices, and staff operations.</p></div>
      <div class="card"><h3>Kitchen Display</h3><p>Pending, cooking, and done stages so the back of house works from a clear queue.</p></div>
      <div class="card"><h3>Waiter Portal</h3><p>Table map, guest sessions, dine-in orders, kitchen fire, and bill generation.</p></div>
      <div class="card"><h3>Reservations</h3><p>Chat-based table booking with guest count, date, time, and special request handling.</p></div>
      <div class="card"><h3>Delivery Workflow</h3><p>Driver assignment, status tracking, proof of delivery, and customer progress updates.</p></div>
      <div class="card"><h3>Invoices & Settlements</h3><p>Billing, paid status, direct/platform settlement visibility, and daily reconciliation support.</p></div>
      <div class="card"><h3>Analytics</h3><p>Top dishes, peak hours, revenue patterns, repeat behavior, and operational KPIs.</p></div>
      <div class="card"><h3>Multi-Outlet Readiness</h3><p>Separate menus, staff, orders, customers, dashboards, and brand-specific AI assistants by branch.</p></div>
    </div>
    <div class="footer-note"><span>Dzukku Business Brochure</span><span>Product Modules</span></div>
  </section>

  <section class="page">
    <p class="section-kicker">Staff Operations</p>
    <h2>Role-Based Workspaces Make It Easy For Non-Technical Teams</h2>
    <p class="lead">
      A good restaurant system should not overwhelm staff. Dzukku separates work by role so each team sees only the
      controls they need.
    </p>
    <div class="screenshot">
      <img src="assets/business-brochure/01-role-selector.png" alt="Dzukku role selector">
      <h3>One product, three operating rooms</h3>
      <p>Admin/POS manages full operations. Waiter handles floor service. Kitchen handles preparation. This separation improves adoption and keeps work focused.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="grid-3" style="margin-top: 12px;">
      <div class="card"><h3>Admin / POS</h3><p>Orders, menu, staff, payments, deliveries, invoices, reservations, and analytics.</p></div>
      <div class="card"><h3>Waiter</h3><p>Table map, active sessions, cart building, kitchen fire, and checkout support.</p></div>
      <div class="card"><h3>Kitchen</h3><p>Item-level KDS queue with pending, cooking, and done status movement.</p></div>
    </div>
    <div class="footer-note"><span>Dzukku Business Brochure</span><span>Role-Based Workspaces</span></div>
  </section>

  <section class="page">
    <p class="section-kicker">Management View</p>
    <h2>Owner Dashboard: The Daily Business Snapshot</h2>
    <div class="screenshot">
      <img src="assets/business-brochure/03-dashboard.png" alt="Dzukku owner dashboard">
      <h3>Live visibility for owners and managers</h3>
      <p>
        The dashboard gives decision-makers a shift-level picture: total orders, revenue, pending work, delivered orders,
        live sync, kitchen count, and order trends. This helps managers act during the day, not only after closing.
      </p>
    </div>
    <div class="grid-3" style="margin-top: 12px;">
      <div class="card tint"><h3>Sales view</h3><p>Revenue, order count, peak hours, and demand patterns.</p></div>
      <div class="card tint"><h3>Operations view</h3><p>Pending orders, kitchen load, ready orders, and service bottlenecks.</p></div>
      <div class="card tint"><h3>Growth view</h3><p>Top dishes, repeat orders, direct channel adoption, and campaign opportunities.</p></div>
    </div>
    <div class="footer-note"><span>Dzukku Business Brochure</span><span>Owner Dashboard</span></div>
  </section>

  <section class="page">
    <p class="section-kicker">Trackable Work</p>
    <h2>Live Orders: Every Customer Request Becomes A Managed Queue</h2>
    <div class="screenshot">
      <img src="assets/business-brochure/09-orders.png" alt="Dzukku live orders view">
      <h3>From customer request to restaurant execution</h3>
      <p>
        The orders screen makes work visible: order references, customer names, ordered items, totals, source channel,
        and current status. This gives the team a shared truth and reduces repeated checking between counter, kitchen,
        delivery, and management.
      </p>
    </div>
    <div class="callout">Business value: fewer lost orders, clearer accountability, faster follow-up, and better service consistency.</div>
    <div class="footer-note"><span>Dzukku Business Brochure</span><span>Order Management</span></div>
  </section>

  <section class="page">
    <p class="section-kicker">Floor And Kitchen</p>
    <h2>Built For Real Restaurant Service</h2>
    <div class="grid-2">
      <div class="screenshot">
        <img src="assets/business-brochure/04-waiter-portal.png" alt="Dzukku waiter portal">
        <h3>Waiter Portal</h3>
        <p>Waiters can open table sessions, see available and occupied tables, manage guests, send orders to kitchen, and complete checkout.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="screenshot">
        <img src="assets/business-brochure/05-kitchen-display.png" alt="Dzukku kitchen display">
        <h3>Kitchen Display</h3>
        <p>Kitchen staff can move every line item from pending to cooking to done while admin and waiter screens stay aligned.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="grid-2" style="margin-top: 12px;">
      <div class="card tint"><h3>Front of house benefit</h3><p>Staff can answer customer questions because kitchen readiness is visible.</p></div>
      <div class="card tint"><h3>Back of house benefit</h3><p>The kitchen gets a structured queue instead of scattered verbal instructions.</p></div>
    </div>
    <div class="footer-note"><span>Dzukku Business Brochure</span><span>Restaurant Operations</span></div>
  </section>

  <section class="page">
    <p class="section-kicker">Customer Experience</p>
    <h2>Customers Order Through A Familiar Chat Interface</h2>
    <p class="lead">
      Dzukku is simple for customers because it does not force them to learn a new app. They can chat, tap quick actions,
      choose direct Dzukku ordering, or use supported delivery channels.
    </p>
    <div class="phone-grid">
      <div class="screenshot phone-shot">
        <img src="assets/business-brochure/06-telegram-dzukku.png" alt="Dzukku direct Telegram ordering">
        <h3>Direct Dzukku Ordering</h3>
        <p>Best for repeat customers, QR ordering, table ordering, packaging links, and social campaigns.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="screenshot phone-shot">
        <img src="assets/business-brochure/07-swiggy-assistant.png" alt="Dzukku Swiggy assistant">
        <h3>Swiggy Channel Support</h3>
        <p>Customers who prefer Swiggy can still be guided through a familiar conversational path.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="screenshot phone-shot">
        <img src="assets/business-brochure/08-zomato-assistant.png" alt="Dzukku Zomato assistant">
        <h3>Zomato Channel Support</h3>
        <p>Dzukku can preserve flexibility while direct ordering remains the preferred repeat-customer path.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="footer-note"><span>Dzukku Business Brochure</span><span>Customer Chat Ordering</span></div>
  </section>

  <section class="page">
    <p class="section-kicker">Business Value</p>
    <h2>Why Businesses Should Consider Dzukku</h2>
    <div class="grid-2">
      <div class="card">
        <h3>More direct customer relationships</h3>
        <p>Restaurants can promote QR and chat ordering to repeat customers instead of depending only on marketplace apps.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="card">
        <h3>Lower operational confusion</h3>
        <p>Orders, kitchen readiness, table sessions, and delivery status become visible in one workflow.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="card">
        <h3>Better customer experience</h3>
        <p>Customers get quick replies, menu help, simple buttons, clear confirmation, and familiar ordering channels.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="card">
        <h3>Management-grade visibility</h3>
        <p>Owners can track revenue, pending orders, top dishes, peak hours, service delays, and growth opportunities.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
    <table>
      <thead>
        <tr>
          <th>Business Area</th>
          <th>Expected Improvement</th>
          <th>How To Measure</th>
        </tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr>
          <td>Direct ordering</td>
          <td>More orders through restaurant-owned channels.</td>
          <td>QR scans, chat starts, completed direct orders.</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td>Kitchen execution</td>
          <td>Fewer missed items and clearer preparation status.</td>
          <td>Prep time, ready time, delayed orders, corrections.</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td>Revenue quality</td>
          <td>More repeat customers and stronger average order value.</td>
          <td>Repeat rate, AOV, add-on acceptance, campaign response.</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td>Management control</td>
          <td>Better decisions on staffing, menu, offers, and branches.</td>
          <td>Peak-hour reports, item sales, status mix, trend dashboards.</td>
        </tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>
    <div class="footer-note"><span>Dzukku Business Brochure</span><span>Business Value</span></div>
