  <section class="page">
    <p class="section-kicker">Use Cases</p>
    <h2>Where Dzukku Fits</h2>
    <div class="grid-2">
      <div class="card"><span class="mini-label">Cloud Kitchen</span><h3>Direct online orders and kitchen discipline</h3><p>Accept direct chat orders, manage prep queues, coordinate delivery, and track demand patterns.</p></div>
      <div class="card"><span class="mini-label">Dine-In Restaurant</span><h3>Table service and kitchen alignment</h3><p>Manage tables, guest sessions, waiter orders, reservations, kitchen tickets, and bills.</p></div>
      <div class="card"><span class="mini-label">Cafe / QSR</span><h3>Quick repeat ordering</h3><p>Make menu browsing, combos, pickup orders, and preparation updates faster for regular customers.</p></div>
      <div class="card"><span class="mini-label">Restaurant Group</span><h3>Multi-outlet control</h3><p>Give each branch separate operations while owners compare performance centrally.</p></div>
    </div>
    <div class="dark-band">
      <h2>Not a replacement for every aggregator use case.</h2>
      <p>
        Swiggy and Zomato remain useful for new customer discovery. Dzukku is strongest for direct ordering, repeat
        customers, dine-in operations, restaurant-owned loyalty, and branch-level management.
